<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-27T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="208" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862.20210/1993: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-27T16:00:00-04:00">October 27, 1942—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1824. My 1813, October 26, 3 p.m. The Minister of Interior has issued
                            strong orders that the investigation of the PYL espionage group be
                            pursued with utmost vigor.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>